metadata.name: My Brain Kaleidoscope
metadata.description:
My grey cells dive into a complex process involving numerous steps that I cannot control.

Every experience of my life wires my brain into a different state of mind. Even when there's no one who wishes harm to me appears to do so and sometimes I pause to reflect back, why would they even want to think about someone in a not so beautiful way?

It takes more than courage for me to protect myself every time my imagination delves into this assumption yet all I know is that I am simply different and my existence is much more than what it appears to be.

Dimensions: 8135 x 7866
Format: Digital Art
